article.headline: Northwestern 88, Arkansas St. 68
article.story: EVANSTON, Ill. (AP) -- Craig Moore had 18 points and five assists to lead Northwestern to a 88-68 win over Arkansas State on Monday. Five players scored in double figures for Northwestern (3-4). Jason Okrzesik scored 16 points, Michael Thompson had 15 points and seven assists, Sterling Williams added 14 points and Nikola Baran had 12 for the Wildcats, who hit a school record 15 3-pointers in 23 attempts. Ryan Wedel scored a career-high 21 for Arkansas State (2-5). Yima Chia-Kur had a career-high 16 points and Shawn Morgan added 10 points. The Indians played without leading scorer Adrian Banks, who averages 21.7 points. Banks was suspended indefinitely after being arrested early Sunday for allegedly firing a gun within Jonesboro, Ark., city limits. Northwestern opened the second half with 15 straight points as part of a 26-6 run and took a 60-40 lead on Thompson's 3-pointer with 11:07 remaining. Arkansas State opened the game on a 11-1 run, with Wedel knocking down three 3-pointers in the first 3:24 of the game. Northwestern closed the first half on a 13-2 streak of their own, including Okrzesik's 3-pointer that tied the game at 34-34.
